  "description": "Build log",
  "body_html": "<p> <em>Thanks to <a href=\"https://www.livingphysics.org/\">David Jordan at Living Physics</a> for the supervision!</em></p><p>I wanted to make an automated setup to test the effect of UV sterilisation of yeast cells at different doses. <a href=\"https://chillphysicsenjoyer.substack.com/p/i-managed-to-grow-countable-yeast\">I now have the concentration that I need to make a countable colony.</a></p><p>To do this, I have a source tube with the solution that I want to irradiate. A pump, which is connected to a relay, pumps it into a cuvette. The cuvette holder has a window where I can shine a different UV lights into it. The pump then finally moves it into the final tube. </p><p>The relay is connected to an Arduino nano so I can control the pump from my mac. I can also connect UV lights to the relay to control the dose from there as well. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!5LuW!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb856bf30-c5e7-4cd5-a768-e8a08db6c008_767x473.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!5LuW!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb856bf30-c5e7-4cd5-a768-e8a08db6c008_767x473.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!5LuW!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb856bf30-c5e7-4cd5-a768-e8a08db6c008_767x473.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!5LuW!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb856bf30-c5e7-4cd5-a768-e8a08db6c008_767x473.png 1272w, https://sub